History Plus is an Google Chrome Extension.
If you install it, default history page(Ctrl-H) is replaced the nice one.
Please go to the page on Chrome Web Store:
https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/mmeiidaaeapionnjaheefgcflidanoeg


-----------------------
Features
-----------------------
 - Select date range easier: Today, Yesterday, Last Week, Last Month, All
 - Select max result number easier: 100, 250, 500, 1000
 - Delete history
 - Grouping same domain in the list
 - Show visit counts each url in the list


-----------------------
How to compile by Closure Compiler
-----------------------
If you have not installed the Closure Compiler,
please visit the official site and read the document.

http://code.google.com/closure/compiler/


the command is below(windows):

1. move to project directory.

> cd "C:\Users\Owner\Develop\Google Chrome Extension\history-plus\git\src"

2. combine files.

> C:\Python27\python.exe "closure-library\closure\bin\build\closurebuilder.py" --root="closure-library" --root="js" --namespace="historyplus.SearchController" --output_mode=compiled --compiler_jar="..\..\..\compiler.jar" --output_file="js\history.min.js"



